<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-x9RBFkfAp816Aw0SpsK0iw" name="mon_proc_imp,_25tFQCMxEd-VobohmWswkw" guid="-x9RBFkfAp816Aw0SpsK0iw" changeDate="2011-07-27T12:24:49.000-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Monitor&amp;nbsp;software development projects in which you have implemented the process and tools improvements in order to&#xD;
    assess performance and compliance. Did you achieve your established goals? Are improvements implemented effectively?&#xD;
    Are they driving the desired business results?&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    From an organizational point of view, this means that you:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Evaluate&amp;nbsp;project performance against established objectives.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Monitor the&amp;nbsp;performance of the&amp;nbsp;capability improvement support environment.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Evaluate the people, the process, and the tools to understand the areas to focus on during the next phase of the&#xD;
    process implementation effort.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Implement a performance measurement system to support timely, informed decisions about process improvements.&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_gChQkG58Ed-ylqwPC08wUA" name="Regularly assess results" guid="_gChQkG58Ed-ylqwPC08wUA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Measure performance, impact, and benefits of the implemented capability improvements. It is important to continuously&#xD;
    assess the process implementation effort as follows:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define measures for improvements (these will vary based on the type of improvement).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Establish baselines.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Monitor&amp;nbsp;project&amp;nbsp;improvement iteration by iteration.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Compare&amp;nbsp;project performance across the organization to performance prior to deployed improvements.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review&amp;nbsp;how&amp;nbsp;projects digests the new process and interview project members to get a feel for the value it&#xD;
    adds.&amp;nbsp;A good time&amp;nbsp;to capture feedback on the process is&amp;nbsp;during project retrospectives. Teams consider&#xD;
    what went well, what they learned about the process, what they would do differently, and what they feel is missing.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Consolidate process and tool improvement requests submitted through the change management process in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.bus.sw_cap_prog_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/reports/process_tool_improvement_log_8E0A6553.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_LpiT4KcUEd-VVeY9V5Zf-g&quot;>Report: Process and Tool Improvement Log&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Another important way to assess performance is by collecting and reviewing measurement data generated from projects.&#xD;
    Produce performance&amp;nbsp;reports&amp;nbsp;and perform analysis&amp;nbsp;at the&amp;nbsp;organizational level against identified&#xD;
    objectives.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Questions to ask as you assess:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Are we on track with our adoption?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Should we adopt additional practices or technology to get more value?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Should we broaden adoption to other groups?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Have our business objectives fundamentally changed?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Use&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.bus.sw_cap_prog_mgmt.base-ibm/workproducts/process_assurance_rev_rec_54B7762.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_EpZOgPNeEd-8OLor5VGqYg&quot;>Artifact: Process Assurance Review Record&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;to objectively and consistently&#xD;
    monitor adoption of the process and tool improvements.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_eOqqcPNcEd-8OLor5VGqYg" name="Monitor tailoring and process usage" guid="_eOqqcPNcEd-8OLor5VGqYg">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Monitor&amp;nbsp;how projects use and&amp;nbsp;tailor the process and tool configurations for their specific needs.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review any deviations from the allowable tailoring standards&amp;nbsp;that occurred. Were the appropriate deviation&#xD;
    approvals obtained?&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Document findings in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.bus.sw_cap_prog_mgmt.base-ibm/workproducts/process_assurance_rev_rec_54B7762.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_EpZOgPNeEd-8OLor5VGqYg&quot;>Artifact: Process Assurance Review Record&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_QZye0G6VEd-ylqwPC08wUA" name="Review and communicate results" guid="_QZye0G6VEd-ylqwPC08wUA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review and communicate adoption and business outcomes. Compile business value and results and conduct reviews with&#xD;
    stakeholders.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Yu1AsG6hEd-ylqwPC08wUA" name="Apply assessment findings" guid="_Yu1AsG6hEd-ylqwPC08wUA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Identify how to improve process assets&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;tool configurations based on lessons learned, measurement data,&#xD;
    and team feedback.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The process is continuously improved based on measurement data and project experience feedback.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_avEZ8G58Ed-ylqwPC08wUA" name="Manage and control changes" guid="_avEZ8G58Ed-ylqwPC08wUA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    As improvements are monitored, change requests are&amp;nbsp;submitted&amp;nbsp;for process definition when the process is a&#xD;
    hindrance or where useful improvements are identified. &amp;nbsp;A group of dedicated resources will analyze the requests&#xD;
    and schedule fixes for future releases of the process.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A change management practice should be adopted to manage changes to process improvement projects. Typical tasks&#xD;
    include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Handle change request&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Assess change request&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Analyze impact&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Approve change&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Follow-up change orders&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Determine corrective action&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>Consolidate process and tool improvement requests submitted through the change management process&amp;nbsp;along&#xD;
with&amp;nbsp;their disposition&amp;nbsp;in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../practice.bus.sw_cap_prog_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/reports/process_tool_improvement_log_8E0A6553.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_LpiT4KcUEd-VVeY9V5Zf-g&quot;>Report: Process and Tool Improvement Log&lt;/a>.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_manage_a_process_and_tools_enhancement_project__activity_definition&quot;&#xD;
name=&quot;XE_manage_a_process_and_tools_enhancement_project__activity_definition&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a&#xD;
id=&quot;XE_process_and_tools_enhancement__managing_a_project&quot; name=&quot;XE_process_and_tools_enhancement__managing_a_project&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this task is to ensure the successful adoption of enhancements to process and tools.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
